{"title_page": "List of universities in Turkey", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a '''list of [[universities]] in [[Turkey]]'''. There are 183 [[university|universities]] and [[academies]] in total: 109 [[Public university|state universities]] (eight [[Technical University|technical universities]], one [[Institute of technology|institutes of technology]], and one [[fine art]]s university), 65 private foundation universities, six two-year granting institutions, one special [[Milli Savunma University|national defense university]], and one [[police academy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.yok.gov.tr/web/guest/universitelerimiz|title=Y\u00d6K \u00dcniversiteler}}</ref>\n\n==Listing by location (provinces)==\n[[File:\u0130stanbul \u00dcniversitesi.JPG|thumb|Entrance of [[Istanbul University]]; founded in 1453, it is the oldest university in Turkey.]]\n[[File:Mk Istanbul Technische Universit\u00e4t.jpg|right|thumb|[[Istanbul Technical University]] (1773), Architecture Faculty in [[Taksim Square|Taksim]]]]\n[[File: Bogazici University.jpg|thumb|right|Faculty of Arts and Sciences, [[Bo\u011fazi\u00e7i University]] (1863), Istanbul]][[File:MarmaraUni.jpg|thumb|right|[[Marmara University]] (1883) campus life in [[Istanbul]]]]\n[[File:Ktu foto 1.jpg|thumb|right|[[Black Sea Technical University]] shore part of [[Kanuni]] campus, [[Trabzon]]]]\n[[File:\u00c7ankaya University Turkuaz campus.JPG|right|thumb|A view of [[\u00c7ankaya University]]'s campus, [[Ankara]]]]\n[[File:The Istanbul Ticaret University.jpg|thumb|[[Istanbul Commerce University]] Eminonu Campus near [[Golden Horn]]]]\n[[File:Iyte entrance gate.jpg|thumb|Entrance gate of [[\u0130zmir Institute of Technology]]]]\n[[File:Ytu 07.jpg|thumb|right|Main building of [[Y\u0131ld\u0131z Technical University]] (1911), Istanbul]]\n[[File:A picture of Campus.jpg|thumb|right|[[Kilis 7 Aral\u0131k University]], [[Kilis]]]]\n[[File:Gazi university.jpg|thumb|right|[[Gazi University]] in Ankara]]