-bowry-2006382|accessdate=7 April 2018|publisher=Kingstonian F.C. Official Site|date=7 April 2018|work=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180409171623/http://www.kingstonian.com/teams/72292/player/dan-bowry-2006382|archive-date=9 April 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Competitions==\n===Friendlies===\nOn 10 May 2017, Charlton Athletic announced [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] would visit during pre-season.<ref>{{Cite news |title=PRE-SEASON {{!}} Ipswich Town friendly confirmed |url=http://www.cafc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/charlton-ipswich-town-201718-pre-season-friendly-3711912.aspx |publisher=Charlton Athletic Official Site |date=10 May 2017 |accessdate=10 May 2017 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Opposition number two and three were announced on 15 May 2017, [[Welling United F.C.|Welling United]] and [[Greenwich Borough F.C.|Greenwich Borough]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=PRE-SEASON {{!}} Welling and Greenwich Borough matches confirmed |url=http://www.cafc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/charlton-pre-season-friendly-welling-united-greenwich-borough-3716247.aspx |publisher=Charlton Athletic Official Site |date=15 May 2017 |accessdate=15 May 2017 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> A day later, Charlton confirmed a trip to [[Dover Athletic F.C.|Dover Athletic]] to the pre-season schedule.<ref>{{Cite news |title=PRE-SEASON {{!}} Dover friendly confirmed |url=http://www.cafc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/charlton-dover-athletic-pre-season-friendly-201718-3717932.aspx |publisher=Charlton Athletic Official Site |date=16 May 2017 |accessdate=16 May 2017 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On 18 May 2017, Charlton announced they would visit [[Republic of Ireland]] as part of their pre-season preparations.<ref>{{Cite news |title=PRE-SEASON {{!}} Irish tour fixtures confirmed |url=http://www.cafc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/charlton-pre-season-ireland-limerick-ucd-crumlin-united-3719650.aspx |publisher=Charlton Athletic Official Site |date=18 May 2017 |accessdate=19 May 2017 |work= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170518161436/http://www.cafc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/charlton-pre-season-ireland-limerick-ucd-crumlin-united-3719650.aspx |archive-date=18 May 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Two more friendlies were revealed a day later.<ref>{{Cite news |title=PRE-SEASON {{!}} Norwich City and Stevenage added to friendly fixtures |url=http://www.cafc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/charlton-norwich-city-stevenage-pre-season-friendly-3720690.aspx |publisher=Charlton Athletic Official Site |date=19 May 2017 |accessdate=19 May 2017 }}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n{{Football box collapsible\n|date = {{Start date|2017|07|10|df=y}}\n|time = 19:45 [[Irish Standard Time|IST]]\n|team1 = [[Crumlin United F.C.|Crumlin United]] {{flagicon|IRE}}\n|score = 0\u20135\n|report = [https://www.cafc.co.uk/news/view/5963ebcf83d91/pre-season-report-crumlin-united-0-charlton-5 Report]\n|team2 = [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]]\n|goals1 = \n|goals2 = [[Tony Watt|Watt]] {{goal|20||34}}<br /> Quinn (og) {{goal|33}}<br /> [[Ricky Holmes|Holmes]] {{goal|73}}<br /> [[Josh Magennis|Magennis]] {{goal|85}}\n|stadium = [[Richmond Park (football ground)|Richmond Park]]\n|location = [[Dublin]], Ireland\n|attendance = \n|referee = \n|result = W\n}}\n{{Football box collapsible\n|date = {{Start date|2017|07|11|df=y}}\n|time = 19:45 [[Irish Standard Time|IST]]\n|team1 = [[Limerick F.C.|Limerick]] {{flagicon|IRE}}\n|score = 3\u20132\n|report = [https://www.cafc.co.uk/news/view/59653ea179d21/pre-season-report-limerick-3-charlton-2 Report]\n|team2 = [[Charlton Athletic F.C.|Charlton Athletic]]\n|goals1 = Kenny {{goal|48}}<br /> Tracy {{goal|56}}<br /> [[Chiedozie Ogbene|Ogbene]] {{goal|79}}\n|goals2 = [[Joe Aribo|Aribo]] {{goal|20}}<br /> [[Josh Magenn